def find_median(nums):
    """
    This function calculates the median of a given list of integers.
    
    Parameters:
    nums (list): A list of integers.
    
    Returns:
    float: The median of the input list.
    """
    nums.sort()
    n = len(nums)
    mid = n / 2
    if n % 2 != 0:
        return nums[mid]
    else:
        return (nums[mid - 1] + nums[mid]) / 2
